# One-Triad First-Budget Seeds Reduce To Three Canonical Helical Sign-Sheet Classes On Ordered Noncollinear Triads

Status: `INFERRED` canonical seed-catalog classification on the frozen Step-1
equivalence sheet

Once repeated-wavevector and collinear relations are removed, every honest
first-budget seed on this branch is an exact triad relation
`k = p + q`
with
`p != q`
and
`p`
not parallel to
`q`,
recorded in one canonical representative ordering
`|p| <= |q|`
with the mirror class chosen once by conjugation.

After quotienting only by the Step-1 equivalences actually frozen on disk,
namely conjugation / mirror choice, global helical-sign relabeling, and the
internal `p <-> q` symmetry, the eight raw helical sign triples reduce to
three canonical classes for
`(sigma_k, sigma_p, sigma_q)`:
`(+++)`,
`(++-)`,
and
`(+--)`.

The current record does not justify collapsing the two mixed-sign classes any
further, and it does not need a finer isosceles-versus-scalene split at this
budget.

