# Step 2 Is Well-Posed Once The Phase Ledger, Search Class, And Metric Sheet Are Frozen

Status: `INFERRED` readiness verdict

Chain Step 2 is now well-posed because the branch has frozen four things on
one exact-support record:

- one admissible intrinsic object, namely the exact triad-phase orbit measure
  on a closed-support ledger;
- one frozen search class, namely finite helical supports with mandatory
  conjugate completion and recursive exact closure;
- one support discipline that includes closure-forced spectators from the
  start and keeps enlargement tests mandatory;
- and one quantitative metric sheet for delayed transfer, spectator burden,
  and robustness.

Later Step-2 work therefore has to enumerate finite helical support ledgers,
not packet-role objects.
It must keep the triad-phase ledger as the surviving phase/coherence object,
treat any scalar coherence score as diagnostic only, keep negative claims
class-limited to the current ladder level and budget, and freeze the formulas
for `J_X`, `tau_turn`, `tau_nu`, the `1/4` target-transfer threshold, the
`1/4` spectator-burden threshold, and the non-single-trajectory robustness
rule before scoring any trajectory.

