+# Meta Note - Step 004 Exploration 003
+
+## What Worked
+
+- Treating the tidy seven-orbit star ledger as a pseudo-survivor only for the
+  enlargement pass kept the step honest while still explaining why Chain Step 3
+  is unearned.
+- Enlarging on a conceptually relevant forced orbit and then watching a simpler
+  mirror-cross difference orbit reappear made the pseudo-survivor diagnosis
+  easy to audit.
+
+## Reusable Lesson
+
+- When a seed dies by first-pass spill, the enlargement pass does not need a
+  complicated new family.
+  It only needs one admissible orbit restoration plus a fresh closure pass to
+  show that pruning was doing all the apparent stabilizing work.
+
+## Caution
+
+- A third-budget negative still remains class-limited.
+  Do not turn a clean pseudo-survivor failure into mission-level termination or
+  automatic escalation.
