 # History of Report Summaries
 
 Exploration summaries will be appended here as they land.
+
+## Exploration 001 Summary
+
+- Goal:
+  classify the canonical third-budget seed families for connected three-triad
+  repeated-wavevector cross-scale clusters.
+- Outcome:
+  `succeeded`.
+- Takeaway:
+  `[INFERRED]` under the frozen Step-1 ladder and the Step-2 / Step-3
+  exclusions, the honest third-budget seed catalog has a single wavevector
+  family only:
+  the seven-orbit three-arm star
+  `{ (a,b,a+b), (a,c,a+c), (a,d,a+d) }`
+  with one repeated orbit `[a]`.
+  Every smaller-support or multi-shared picture either falls back into the
+  exhausted lower budgets or repeats more than one orbit and so lies outside
+  the declared current rung.
+
+## Exploration 002 Summary
+
+- Goal:
+  run the recursive exact closure audit on the canonical third-budget seed
+  family.
+- Outcome:
+  `succeeded`.
+- Takeaway:
+  `[INFERRED]` no honest third-budget seed survives.
+  On the canonical three-arm star
+  `{ (a,b,a+b), (a,c,a+c), (a,d,a+d) }`,
+  mandatory conjugate completion already creates mirror-cross spill targets like
+  `b-a`,
+  `c-a`,
+  and
+  `d-a`,
+  while positive-positive cross-scale pairs give backup spill witnesses such as
+  `a+b+c`.
+  Even the bridge coincidence
+  `d = b+c`
+  only changes which orbit spills first.
+
+## Exploration 003 Summary
+
+- Goal:
+  run the admissible-enlargement audit on any apparent third-budget survivor,
+  or package a clean current-budget negative if none remain.
+- Outcome:
+  `succeeded`.
